OL,6,FA fourth officer was subject to
OL,7,Fmeasures designed to improve his
OL,8,Fperformance following the
OL,9,Finvestigation of the incident in
OL,10,FDecember 2022.
OL,12,FThe man made a complaint to the Police
OL,13,FOmbudsman's Office and submitted a
OL,14,Fseven-hour excerpt in which officers
OL,15,Freferred to a suspected victim of
OL,16,Fdomestic violence as "mental",
OL,17,Fpossibly suffering from "post-natal
OL,18,Fdepression" and requiring admission to
OL,19,Fhospital.
