OL,3,CPSNI officers issued with advice after
OL,4,C'degrading comments'
OL,6,FThe investigation concluded that the
OL,7,Fmobile phone had not been packaged,
OL,8,Flabelled or stored in accordance with
OL,9,FPSNI policy. It had also been taken
OL,10,Fout of the police station while the
OL,11,Fcomplainant was in custody, and there
OL,12,Fwas no clear record of its movements
OL,13,Fwhile in police possession.
OL,15,FAdditionally, Police Ombudsman
OL,16,Finvestigators examined an allegation
OL,17,Fthat an officer had encouraged a
OL,18,Fcolleague to destroy the mobile phone
OL,19,Fout of fear it might be recording and
OL,20,Fanother officer was heard to respond
OL,21,F"what a way to get sacked".
