OL,3,CPSNI officers issued with advice after
OL,4,C'degrading comments'
OL,6,FThe Police Ombudsman identified no
OL,7,Fmisconduct in relation to the
OL,8,Fcomplainant's other allegations, which
OL,9,Fincluded that he had been unlawfully
OL,10,Farrested and that officers had
OL,11,Ffalsified statements and incident
OL,12,Flogs, and caused damage to a laptop
OL,13,Fwhile he had been in police custody.
OL,15,FHugh Hume, chief executive for the
OL,16,Foffice of the Police Ombudsman, said
OL,17,Fthe remarks were concerning.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/12
